<$fill $name="body">

!! Basic comparison

Select two tiddlers in the panel and click Compare. Each differing field appears as a collapsible section:

* ''Single-line fields'' (e.g., `tags`, `caption`, `modified`) show source and target values side by side. A toggle lets you pick which value to keep.
* ''Multiline fields'' (e.g., `text`) show line-by-line hunks with deleted lines in red and inserted lines in green. Each hunk has its own source/target toggle.

Fields that exist in only one tiddler are marked with a ''+'' (target-only) or ''&minus;'' (source-only) badge.

!! Selective sync workflow

# Compare two tiddlers
# In the `text` field, you might see three hunks. Toggle hunk 1 to "source" (keep the source version of those lines) and leave hunks 2 and 3 on "target" (accept the target changes)
# For the `tags` field, toggle to "source" to keep the source's tags
# Click ''Apply to target'' -- the target tiddler is updated with your selected mix of changes
# Or click ''Apply to source'' to write in the opposite direction

!! Using the widget directly

You can use `<$action-diffsync>` in your own wikitext outside the panel:

```
<$button>
  <$action-diffsync op="compare" source="Meeting Notes" target="Meeting Notes (draft)"/>
  Compare notes
</$button>
```

After comparison, read the result from `$:/temp/diffsync/result`:

```
<$list filter="[[$:/temp/diffsync/result]get[text]jsonindexes[]]" variable="idx">
  Field: <$text text={{{ [[$:/temp/diffsync/result]get[text]jsonget<idx>,[field]] }}}/>
</$list>
```

!! Integration with minver

If you use the minver plugin for tiddler versioning, you can compare a current tiddler against a snapshot:

# In minver, select a snapshot and use "Materialize" to write it to a temporary tiddler
# In diffsync, set the materialized snapshot as the source and the current tiddler as the target
# Compare to see exactly what changed since that snapshot
# Selectively roll back specific hunks by toggling them to "source" and applying

!! Adjusting context lines

By default, 3 lines of unchanged text are shown around each change. Adjust this in ''Settings > diffsync'' or by editing `$:/config/rimir/diffsync/context-lines`. Setting it to `0` shows only the changed lines; higher values give more surrounding context. Changes take effect on the next comparison.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
